3. API Endpoints
Wallets — /wallets
Method	Path	Body/Query	Description
GET	/wallets	—	List all wallets for current user
POST	/wallets	{ name, bank, last4?, color?, walletType?, balance? }	Create wallet
PATCH	/wallets/:id	partial wallet fields	Update wallet
DELETE	/wallets/:id	—	Delete wallet
GET	/wallets/summary	—	{ totalBalance, walletCount } for home screen
Transactions — /transactions
Method	Path	Body/Query	Description
GET	/transactions	?type=income|expense|all&category=food&walletId=&page=1&limit=20	Paginated list with filters
GET	/transactions/recent	?limit=3	For home screen
GET	/transactions/history	?category=food&month=4&year=2026	Grouped by date (TODAY/YESTERDAY/date)
POST	/transactions	{ type, category, title, description?, amount, date?, walletId?, receiptUrl? }	Create transaction (also updates wallet balance)
PATCH	/transactions/:id	partial fields	Update
DELETE	/transactions/:id	—	Delete (also reverses wallet balance)
Grouping logic for /history:

Group by date field (not createdAt)
Label: if date == today → "TODAY", if yesterday → "YESTERDAY", else → "MON APR 28"
Sort groups descending, items descending within group
Balance update rule:

On POST INCOME: wallet.balance += amount
On POST EXPENSE: wallet.balance -= amount
On DELETE: reverse the above
Reports — /reports
Method	Path	Query	Description
GET	/reports/monthly	?year=2026&months=6	Last N months total spending per month (bar chart)
GET	/reports/by-category	?month=4&year=2026	Spending breakdown per category (pie chart)
GET	/reports/summary	?month=4&year=2026	{ totalIncome, totalExpense, net }
GET	/reports/top-expenses	?month=4&year=2026&limit=4	Top N expense transactions (for list in reports)
monthly response shape:

[{ "month": "Nov", "year": 2025, "total": 645.20 }, ...]
by-category response shape:

[{ "category": "food", "label": "Food", "amount": 318.00, "percentage": 36.8 }, ...]
Budget — /budget
Method	Path	Body	Description
GET	/budget/current	—	Budget for current month: { limit, spent, remaining, percentage }
PUT	/budget	{ limit, month?, year? }	Create or update budget for a month
spent is computed live from transactions (SUM of EXPENSE for that month).

OCR — /ocr
Method	Path	Body	Description
POST	/ocr/scan-receipt	multipart image file	Extract amount + merchant from receipt image
Response:

{ "amount": 84.30, "merchant": "Whole Foods", "date": "2026-04-30", "confidence": 0.87 }
OCR library: tesseract.js (runs in Node, no external API needed). Parse strategy:

Run OCR on image
Regex for total amount: /total[\s:]*\$?([\d,]+\.?\d{0,2})/i
First non-number line as merchant candidate
Date regex: /(jan|feb|mar|apr|may|jun|jul|aug|sep|oct|nov|dec)[\s,]+\d{1,2}/i
